From Dave Weaver Subject Some questions from a new Christian In a previous article Steven R Hoskins writes One of my questions I would like to ask is Can anyone recommend a good reading list of theological works intended for a lay person I would recommend Essential Truthes of the Christian Faith by RC It is copywrited from Tyndale House Sproul offers concise explanations in simple language of around different Christian doctrines grouped by I think it would be particularly good for newer Christians and older Christians suffering spiritual malnutrition as it gives a Biblically sound basic treatment of the issues avoiding long in depth analysis that can wait until after you know the Dave Weaver He is no fool who gives what he cannot keep to gain what he cannot Jim Elliot